		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Product feature mining is a key subtask in fine-grained opinion mining . <S>\r",
			"relation": "bg-compare"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "Previous works often use syntax constituents in this task . <S>\r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "However , syntax-based methods can only use discrete contextual information , \r",
			"relation": "contrast"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "which may suffer from data sparsity . <S>\r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "This paper proposes a novel product feature mining method \r",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "which leverages lexical and contextual semantic clues . <S>\r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Lexical semantic clue verifies whether a candidate term is related to the target product , \r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "and contextual semantic clue serves as a soft pattern miner \r",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "to find candidates , \r",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "which exploits semantics of each word in context \r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "so as to alleviate the data sparsity problem . <S>\r",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "We build a semantic similarity graph \r",
			"relation": "elab-process_step"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "to encode lexical semantic clue , \r",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "and employ a convolutional neural model \r",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 14,
			"text": "to capture contextual semantic clue . <S>\r",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 16,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Then Label Propagation is applied to combine both semantic clues . <S>\r",
			"relation": "elab-process_step"
		},
		{
			"id": 17,
			"parent": 18,
			"text": "Experimental results show \r",
			"relation": "attribution"
		},
		{
			"id": 18,
